4. quesdo Classes

    Used mostly with links and interactive elements.
      :link — unvisited links
      :visited — visited links
      :hover — mouse is over the element
      :active — element is being clicked
      :focus — element has keyboard/mouse focus
      :target — element targeted by a URL fragment (#id)

    📝 Form & Input States
    Mainly for form controls and validation.
      :checked — checked inputs (checkbox, radio)
      :disabled — disabled elements
      :enabled — enabled elements
      :required — required inputs
      :optional — optional inputs
      :valid — input passes validation
      :invalid — input fails validation

    🌳 Structural (Tree-Based) Selectors
      Based on the element’s position in the DOM.
      :root — the root element (<html>)
      :empty — elements with no children
      :first-child
      :last-child
      :nth-child(n)
      :nth-last-child(n)
      :only-child

    🧩 Type-Based Structural Selectors
    Like structural selectors, but scoped to element type.
      :first-of-type
      :last-of-type
      :nth-of-type(n)
      :only-of-type

    🧠 Logical / Functional Pseudo-Classes

    Used for advanced selector logic and grouping.
      :not(selector) — excludes elements
      :is(selector) — matches any selector in the list
      :where(selector) — same as :is() but with zero specificity

